

Space Hulk
Demo instructions 17/08/93

1.      Put your Space Hulk demo disk in your internal disk drive and 
	turn your Amiga on.

2.      Bypass the loading screen by using the left mouse button.

3.      Load Space Hulk by clicking on 'Start New Mission' on the mission 
	select screen.

4.      The Imperial Commander welcomes you and explains the basic mission 
	plan. Left click after every sentence and then move to the detailed 
	mission briefing. Using the map of the Hulk that appears on the 
	left of the screen, the Commander goes through the initial points of 
	deployment, objectives and pick-up areas for the victorious squad.
	Left click to the end of the briefing.
	You are now transported to the Space Hulk.

5.      Only one of the view screens is active. The view gives you the 
	display from Terminator number 1 (note the number in the top left 
	of the display). The letters next to the Terminator tell you 
	what weapon he is carrying.
	The Terminator in this mission carries a Storm Bolter (SB) and a 
	Power Glove (PG).

	Left click on the Freeze Time On/Off button to bring the game out 
	of Freeze Time and into Real Time. When the game is in Real Time 
	everything happens at it's normal speed.

	Example: A Genestealer that becomes "frozen" by the use of the Freeze 
	Time can thunder down the corridor towards you during Real Time.

6.      Control the Terminator by using the mouse or cursor keys. As you 
	move the mouse pointer to the edges of the View Screen it changes 
	into a directional arrow indicating the possible command - to move 
	in that direction left click. Using the mouse control move the 
	Terminator down the corridor to the door. As you move, watch the 
	Scanner in the lower left portion of the screen. The brown blip is 
	the Primary Terminator. As you move, so the Scanner follows your 
	progress through the Hulk.

7.      Press the UP cursor once to open the door. Practice turns and walking 
	backwards to get the feel of the controls. Notice the scanner 
	in the left of the screen moves as you do.

8.      Move the mouse pointer into the centre of the View Screen. The arrow 
	changes to a cross-hair. left click and watch a from your Storm 
	Bolter shoot off down the corridor and explode against the wall.
	Move your Terminator back to the original starting position. Left 
	click on the Freeze Time button.

9.      Right click on the scanner to go to the Planning Screen.

	Left click on the Move icon (top left) and left click again at the 
	end of the corridor you're in. 
	The program decides the quickest route, red arrows show the movement 
	you have constructed. Using this screen it is possible to program the 
	Terminators with other commands. From top left;

Move                    -       Initialises the Terminator for movement
Turn                    -       Using left and right mouse buttons, the 
				Terminator can be made to turn.
Fire                    -       Using this button it is possible to fire 
				your selected weapon.
Open/Close              -       Using this with left and right mouse buttons 
				will open doors.

Number of shots         -       Selects how many times your Terminator will 
				fire.
Terminator select       -       This tells you who you are commanding and 
				the weapon he is carrying.

Order phases            -       Indicates the commands you have given the 
				selected Terminator.

Range of fire           -       This will give you an indication of where 
				your Terminator can fire to.
Switch squads           -       Used to switch between squads in multi squad 
				missions.
Cancel command          -       Cancels the Terminators last command.
Go                      -       Gets the Terminator moving.

Freeze Time             -       This button switches between real and freeze 
				time.
Freeze Time bar         -       This bar tells you how much planning time 
				you have available.

Strategic map           -       This map gives you an overview of the whole 
				Hulk.


10.     Once you have your Terminator programmed, use the right mouse button 
	to return to the Action Screen. Click on Freeze Time to return to 
	Real Time and watch the Terminator carry out the programmed moves.

11.     Locate the item in the Hulk and pick it up using the right mouse 
	button.

12.     Destroy the statue and prepare for the Genestealers. Take care not 
	to become too trigger happy or you will find your gun jamming.

13.     Return to the entrance, closing the door behind you by clicking on 
	the right side of the door with the right mouse button.

Congratulations! You have completed the first mission.
